args: The duo's arrival at the dunefolk settlement\nis marked by a pair of unexpected events.
One is an imperial attack. The other...
Stomp it out down the runway,\nthen VOGUE! Boom!
That was perfect, Ria. Totes nasty!
...The other is a fashion show held at the dunefolk\nfestivalâ€”an event in which both Nadine and\nNefaria have been asked to participate.
Seriously, you're slaying it.\nI've got nothing left to teach you.
I am gladdened to hear it, and pray only\nthat my performance might entertain\nthe audience.
The scions of the Sandreach are forsooth a\npeople most stout-hearted; even an armed\nincursion has not dulled their enthusiasm.
I will do all in my power to\nreward such perseverance.
Oh, for sure. I can't wait to hit the runway\nwith you, girl! It's gonna be great!
Oh, and speaking of things I can't wait for,\nI totally blanked that we had a date to go\ncheck out the festival!
We gotta get on that. Let's go, Ria!
Fie, Nadine! You needn't tear my arm\nfrom my body!
Ooo, I like the smell of what's cookin'...\nCheck out all the food stalls!
I totally don't even know where to start.\nWhat're you thinkin', girl?
I need nothing more. I am sated.
Say whaaat? We haven't eaten yet!
'Tis my breast that is full to bursting,\nnot my stomach.
The scions of the kingdom I lost live on,\nembracing life and all its myriad joys.
This sight alone leaves my heart replete.
Ohmigosh, I'm totally gonna bawl.\nThat was SO sweet!
But seriously, we need to eat something.
Heck, maybe some familiar flavors\nwill spark a memory or three, yeah?
Wh-what is this sensation?! Nostalgia's\npangs mingle with a burgeoning hunger\nthat wells up from the core of my being!
*sniff* *sniiiiff* Oh yeah, it's def those\nkebabs at the stall over there.
They say the flavor all comes down to a\nsecret spice blend that's been passed\ndown through the generations!
Then there might be a chance\nI tasted such meat myself long ago\nand longer still!
See? What'd I tell you? The head might\nforget, but the gut ALWAYS remembers.
We gotta try a bite so you can\nfind out for sure!
*drool* Y-you make a compelling case...\nLet us indulge ourselves, then.
NOW it's starting to feel like a festival!
Yeah, I can't even right now.
Aw, boo. Guess the only thing this\nbrought back to you was an appetite.
B-but surely 'tis too soon to acquiesce!\nAnother delicacy may yet yield results!
Hey, it's worth a shot! Leave it to meâ€”\nI got the hot tips on the tastiest treats!
Then I shall rely upon your wisdom.
Girl, I am game to stuff my face until\nwe get ALL of your memories back.
Ooof. We did a couple laps of the meat-\nveg-tea-dessert loop and I am BURSTING!
Bummer it didn't shake loose any of your\nold memories, but at least we had fun!
Don't you think, Ria? ...Uhh, Ria?\nHey, where'd she go?
'Tis no cause for concern;\nI am weary, nothing more.
Guess I had us hit the ol' food-stall\ncircuit a little too hard, huh?
You've naught to apologize for.\nThe fault is my own.
In my excitement, I lost all sight\nof temperance.
Yet you have my gratitude; this has all\nbeen a most happy experience.
Alas, this ï¼‚festival dateï¼‚ indulgence nears\nits end, as all good things must.
For to fraternize with the people here any\nlonger poses too great a risk of revealing\nmy true identity.
Okay, then just ooooone more spot.\nLast one, I promise!
Yet to tempt fortune any further wouldâ€”
I know! But there's one thing left I just\nHAVE to show you. Pleeease?
Fie, Nadine... Very well. But only one!
You are. The BEST. Okay, let's go!
